The South African Hajj and Umrah Council (SAHUC) announced on 24 March that the second Hajj Awareness Programmes planned for 4 April in Cape Town and 5 April in Johannesburg will be postponed until further notice. This is due to the nationwide lockdown called by President Cyril Ramaphosa commencing from Thursday, 26 March. The SAHUC offices will be closed from Thursday, 26 March until 16 April during the lockdown period. SAHUC will inform the public of any developments with regard to Hajj 2020/1441 AH if and when  official communication is received from the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah. SAHUC will also await a directive from the South African government pertaining to travel restrictions. For all hajj and umrah matters or queries contact 010 020 7400 or email: info@sahuc.org.za Also read: https://tabloidmedia.co.za/ethekwini-secure-ready-for-lockdown-challenge/